<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Overview">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>The Fujin can carry M-class cargo and hence the <a href="/index.php/Triplex_Scanner" title="Triplex Scanner" class="mw-redirect">Triplex Scanner</a>, making it along with the <a href="/index.php/Discoverer" title="Discoverer">Discoverer</a> and <a href="/index.php/Kestrel" title="Kestrel">Kestrel</a> one of the better scout craft.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Variants">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Variants">Variants</span></h2>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Fujin">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Fujin">Fujin</span></h3>
<p>Not featuring any fancy title, the basic version of the ship is the standard by which other variants are measured.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Fujin Raider">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Fujin_Raider">Fujin Raider</span></h3>
<p>Raider variants are faster and usually have a higher shield generator power than their regular counterparts, but trade off cargo capacity and some have reduced shield capacity despite the more powerful generator.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Fujin Sentinel">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Fujin_Sentinel">Fujin Sentinel</span></h3>
<p>Sentinel variants of ships tend to be slower, but with higher total shield capacity. Sometimes the shield class is also upgraded for instance from 25 MJ to 200 MJ.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Physical Characteristics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Physical_Characteristics">Physical Characteristics</span></h2>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Combat">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Combat"> Combat </span></h2>
<p>Scout ships like the Fujin are too weak to fare well in dogfights.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Equipment">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Equipment"> Equipment </span></h2>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Availability">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Availability"> Availability </span></h2>
<p>The Fujin can be bought at the Yaki Shipyard in <a href="/index.php/Senator%27s_Badlands" title="Senator's Badlands">Senator's Badlands</a>.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Fujin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Suggested Roles">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Suggested_Roles"> Suggested Roles</span></h2>
